Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Candente Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-02-11T21:50:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-candente-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell for a fourth session, dropping
0.4 percent to 22,772.10. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid
0.1 percent to 3,059.07.  Gold and silver miners dropped after futures declined in
New York, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell for a fourth session, losing
1.5 percent to $40.01. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE),
Peru’s biggest silver producer, dropped 0.7 percent to 4.07
soles. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc mining company, fell for a sixth session,
declining 1.4 percent to 1.38 soles.  Copper shares fell after the metal slumped in New York.    Alturas Minerals Corp . (ALT PE), a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 4.2 percent to 23 cents.  Candente
Copper Corp . (DNT PE), a Canadian exploration company, fell 1.3
percent to $2.21.    Maple Energy Plc . (MPLE PE), the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, dropped 3.5 percent to $1.11
after crude oil fell to a 10-week low in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
